# Capital Call Notice

Formal notice demanding capital contributions under the governing agreement with precise calculations and payment mechanics.

## Prerequisites

1. Governing agreement(s): LPA/LLC operating agreement, subscription agreements, amendments, side letters.
2. Notice provisions: authorized purposes, notice period, delivery method, cure/default process, governing law.
3. Fund/entity details: legal name, GP/manager name, signatory authority, address, letterhead.
4. Investor schedule: commitments, contributions to date, remaining unfunded, ownership percentage.
5. Capital call purpose: investment or expense description, amount breakdown, compliance with permitted uses.
6. Payment instructions: beneficiary, bank, ABA/SWIFT, account number, reference codes, alternate methods.
7. Contact details for questions and payment confirmation routing.

## Output Structure / Process

**Intake Checklist**

| Item | Required Detail | Source |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Governing document citation | Full title, execution date, section numbers authorizing calls and remedies | LPA/Operating Agreement |
| Notice period | Minimum days, delivery method, timing rule | Notice clause |
| Allocation method | Pro rata or specified formula, side-letter deviations | Capital call provisions |
| Call purpose | Investment/expense/reserve and permitted use basis | Investment memo/budget |
| Default remedies | Interest rate, dilution/forfeiture, suspension, cure period | Default clause |
| Wire instructions | Bank name, address, ABA, SWIFT, account name/number | Treasury |

**Capital Call Schedule (attach as exhibit or appendix)**

| Investor | Commitment | Contributed to Date | Unfunded Commitment | Ownership % | Amount Due | Notes/Side Letter |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| {Investor Name} | {$$} | {$$} | {$$} | {%%} | {$$} | {If any} |

**Calculation Statement**

Use one paragraph that states the formula and confirms compliance with the agreement (e.g., pro rata based on commitments unless modified by side letters). Include aggregate amount called and total fund commitment base.

**Letter Template**

```text
[Fund Letterhead]

Date: {Month DD, YYYY}

To: {Investor Legal Name}
Attn: {Contact Name/Title}
Address: {Address}

Re: Capital Call Notice under {Agreement Title} dated {Agreement Date}

Dear {Investor Name}:

Pursuant to Section {##} of the {Agreement Title} dated {Agreement Date} (the "Agreement"), the General Partner/Manager hereby issues this Capital Call Notice for the Fund's authorized purposes described below.

1. Aggregate Call Amount: {Total Amount}.
2. Your Pro Rata Amount Due: {Investor Amount}.

Purpose of Call: {Brief purpose aligned with permitted uses; include high-level investment/expense categories without disclosing restricted confidential details}.

Payment Due Date: {Month DD, YYYY} by {Time} {Time Zone}. This notice provides not less than the minimum notice period required under Section {##} of the Agreement.

Payment Instructions:
Beneficiary: {Account Name}
Bank: {Bank Name}, {Bank Address}
ABA/Routing: {ABA}
SWIFT: {SWIFT}
Account No.: {Account Number}
Reference: {Reference Code / Investor ID}

Please email wire confirmation to {Email} with {Required details}.

Default Remedies: Failure to fund by the due date may result in the remedies set forth in Section {##} of the Agreement, including {list exact remedies and any cure period, if applicable}.

Questions: {Contact Name}, {Title}, {Phone}, {Email}.

Sincerely,

{Authorized Signatory}
{Title}
{General Partner/Manager Entity}
```

**Default Remedies Matrix (insert exact terms)**

| Remedy | Trigger | Source Section | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Default interest | Late payment | §{##} | Rate and accrual start date |
| Dilution/forfeiture | Failure to cure | §{##} | Formula and timing |
| Distribution suspension | Default status | §{##} | Duration |
| Forced transfer | Continued default | §{##} | Process and valuation |

**Delivery Method**

State the delivery method required by the notice clause and confirm delivery address or email on record.

## Guidelines

- Match every citation to the governing agreement; do not paraphrase section numbers.
- Use full month names for dates and specify time zone for the deadline.
- Do not exceed authorized purposes; tie each use to the agreement.
- Reflect side letter modifications only for the applicable investor and keep other terms confidential.
- State remedies exactly as written; include cure periods or required follow-up notices.
- Verify signatory authority and entity names against formation and management docs.
- Include only necessary investment context; avoid disclosing non-public deal terms unless permitted.
- Confirm delivery method and addresses comply with notice provisions and any electronic delivery requirements.
- Mirror the governing law and jurisdiction clause; do not introduce new law terms.
- Keep amounts consistent across letter body and schedule; re-check arithmetic.
